-- S. Africa to Re-Erect Fence With Mozambique, SAPA Says
-- B y   H i l t o n   S h o n e
-- 2012-01-16T12:48:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-16/s-africa-to-re-erect-fence-with-mozambique-sapa-says-correct-.html
(Corrects spelling of name in headline and first
paragraph.)  South African officials met to
discuss re-erecting a 150-kilometer fence along the Mozambique
border, the South African Press Association reported, citing
Environmental Affairs spokesman Mandla Mathebula.  The fence is to help curb rhinoceros poaching in the Kruger
National Park, SAPA said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
